This file describes changes in recent versions of cerebro. It
primarily documents those changes that are of interest to users and
admins.

Changes in cerebro-1.19-1
===========================
 -- Fix LSB compliance with cerebrod init script.
 -- Fix chkconfig end priority.

Changes in cerebro-1.18-1
===========================
 -- Fix segfault corner case when non-resolving hostname passed into
    libcerebro.

Changes in cerebro-1.17-1
===========================
 -- Support cerebrod_monitor_module_exclude,
    cerebrod_event_module_exclude, and
    cerebrod_gettimeofday_workaround options.

Changes in cerebro-1.16-1
===========================
 -- Limit debug output in cerebrod only when running in the
    foreground.
 
Changes in cerebro-1.15-1
===========================
 -- Allow -d and -c in production builds of cerebrod.
 -- Allow debug flags in cerebro.conf in production builds of cerebro.

Changes in cerebro-1.14-1
===========================
 -- Various documentation updates.

Changes in cerebro-1.13-1
===========================
 -- Fix portability bug for 32 bit vs 64 bit machines.
 -- Fix build issues for RHEL6.
 -- Various documentation updates.

Changes in cerebro-1.12-1
===========================
 -- Increase verbosity of error logging to aid in debugging.

Changes in cerebro-1.11-1
===========================
 -- Include cerebro.conf template by default.

Changes in cerebro-1.10-1
===========================
 -- Fix corner cases with event modules specifying multiple events.
 -- Fix documentation typos.
 -- Various minor bug fixes.

Changes in cerebro-1.9-1
===========================
 -- Do not enable cerebrod daemon by default.

Changes in cerebro-1.8-1
===========================
 -- Fix spec file build issue.

Changes in cerebro-1.7-1
===========================
 -- Fix cerebrod race/crash corner case.

Changes in cerebro-1.6-1
===========================
 -- Fix cerebrod initialization race.
 -- Fix cerebrod error output messages.
 -- Fix config file parsing corner case.
 -- Fix documentation typos.

Changes in cerebro-1.5-1
===========================
 -- Fix mem-corruption bug.

Changes in cerebro-1.4-1
===========================
 -- Various bug fixes.

Changes in cerebro-1.3-1
===========================
 -- Redo configuration file format for message listening and speaking.
 -- Support message forwarding.
 -- Support module versioning.

Changes in cerebro-1.2-1
===========================
 -- Documentation updates

Changes in cerebro-1.1-1
===========================
 -- Allow cerebro to work on multiple subnets.
 -- Added load average, memory, and network traffic metric modules.
 -- Support event based monitoring.
 -- Various bug fixes.

Changes in cerebro-1.0-4
===========================
 -- Added graceful shutdown metric module.
 -- Allow monitor modules to support multiple metrics.
 -- Various bug fixes.

Changes in cerebro-1.0-1
===========================
 -- Initial Release

$Id: NEWS,v 1.17 2010-06-01 21:01:37 chu11 Exp $
